OT	Heirloom Tomato BLTs
FO	Serve 4
NO	Colorful, flavorful heirloom tomatoes star in these classic sandwiches. Also try making a BLT salad: stir the mayonnaise and pesto into 2 tablespoons of your favorite vinaigrette, then toss with lots of chopped lettuce, tomatoes, crumbled bacon or tempeh, and homemade croutons.
OT	Ingredients
IN	8 slices whole-grain sandwich bread, grilled or toasted
IN	2 tablespoons mayonnaise or vegan mayonnaise
IN	1 tablespoon prepared pesto or vegan pesto (optional)
IN	1 pound assorted heirloom tomatoes (2 to 3), sliced
IN	Finishing salt, such as fleur de sel or Maldon
IN	8 ounces bacon, cooked crisp, or tempeh bacon strips, cooked according to package instructions
IN	1 cup chopped lettuce
OT	Method
PR	Lay bread out on a work surface. Combine mayonnaise and pesto; spread evenly over one side of each bread slice. Sprinkle tomatoes with salt and layer onto half the bread slices. Top tomatoes with bacon and lettuce, and cover with remaining bread slices. Cut each sandwich in half on the diagonal and pile onto a platter.
